author: Source: Star Tribune
title: Blue Jays break out bats in Game 3 victory - Star Tribune
text:
Ryan Goins, who earlier drove in two runs with a single, hit the Blue Jays' third home run of Monday's game, a solo shot. - Troy Tulowitzki, Josh Donaldson and the slugging Toronto Blue Jays were eager to return to their homer dome after dropping the first two games of the American League Championship Series at Kansas City.
 Star Tribune.
